sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant B as Browser (UaClient)
    participant WST as WebSocketTransport
    participant WS as WsServer
    participant RT as opcua::ServerRuntime
    participant S as ServerSession
    participant M as ServerSessionManager
    participant SEC as SecurityService

    Note over B,WST: WebSocketTransport accepts WS/WSS and enforces<br/>path, subprotocol, and allowed Origin
    B->>WST: GET /ua<br/>Upgrade: websocket<br/>Sec-WebSocket-Protocol: opcua+uajson<br/>Origin: https://scada.local
    WST->>WST: validate path + subprotocol + allowed origin
    WST-->>B: 101 Switching Protocols
    WST->>WS: accepted websocket transport
    B->>S: requestHandle=1<br/>CreateSessionRequest (JSON)
    S->>RT: decoded request envelope
    RT->>M: CreateSession(requestedTimeout)
    M-->>S: SessionId + AuthenticationToken + ServerNonce + RevisedTimeout
    S-->>B: requestHandle=1<br/>CreateSessionResponse

    B->>S: requestHandle=2<br/>ActivateSessionRequest<br/>(UserNameIdentityToken: PBKDF2(password, nonce))
    S->>RT: decoded request envelope
    RT->>M: ActivateSession(sessionId, token, credentials)
    M->>SEC: authenticate(user, token)
    SEC-->>M: identity accepted
    M-->>RT: attached session + scada::ServiceContext
    RT->>S: attach/create ServerSession
    S-->>B: requestHandle=2<br/>ActivateSessionResponse

    Note over B,M: Data plane opens after the session is attached
    Note over B,RT: Implemented in common today: opcua::ServerRuntime routes decoded request bodies<br/>through ServerSessionManager, ServerSession, and opcua::ServiceHandler

    Note over B,S: Connection drops, browser reconnects before timeout
    S->>RT: disconnect / detach
    RT->>M: DetachSession(authenticationToken)
    B->>S: requestHandle=3<br/>ActivateSessionRequest(sessionId, token)
    S->>RT: decoded request envelope
    RT->>M: ActivateSession(resume)
    M-->>RT: resumed attached session
    RT->>S: reattach existing ServerSession
    S-->>B: requestHandle=3<br/>ActivateSessionResponse(resumed=true)

    B->>S: requestHandle=4<br/>CloseSessionRequest
    S->>RT: decoded request envelope
    RT->>M: CloseSession(sessionId, token)
    M-->>S: session removed
    S-->>B: requestHandle=4<br/>CloseSessionResponse
    WST-->>B: Close frame (1000)
